# Go Backend Conventions

- Keep backend code inside `backend/internal/`.
- Domain packages should follow `handler.go`, `service.go`, `model.go`.
- Handlers should stay thin: parse request, call service, return JSON.
- Use `pgx` with raw SQL. Do not introduce an ORM.
- Use typed app errors via `internal/apperrors`.
- Keep route registration centralized in `cmd/server/main.go`.
- Prefer constructor injection (`NewService`, `NewHandler`) over globals.
- Keep migration files as numbered SQL pairs in `internal/db/migrations/`.
